b'     Dear Students,        Link       Oneyear exchanges at Centrale Nantes commence at the beginning of September. If you are interested in a shorter programme, semester exchanges are also proposed for both the autumn and spring semesters, commencing respectively in September and February.    Please find the link for further info here       See the list of courses available for a year, autumn or spring semester exchange and download your learning agreement:    Courses taught in French   &nb;sp; How to Apply?   1.    Contact oir4@wmail.iitm.ac.in (or) oir4.iitm@gmail.com to complete the nomination procedure. Only students nominated by home university coordinator will be eligible to apply.  2.     Check out the course list and language of instruction  3.    Register online beforethe deadline.( 15th May for the exchange year and the autumn semester, 31st October for the spring semester)  4.    Download your learning agreement and fill it in according to your chosen courses.  5.    Send the following documents to  international@ecnantes.fr :   a CV (Europass for European students)    a cover letter (in French or English)     your latest transcript of records   your fully complete and signed learning agreement    copy of ID or passport.  Your application will be assessed by the Centrale Nantes commission .  You will be notified of the outcome.  &nb;sp; Academic Calendar 1st / Autumn Semester :<span classD"appleconvertedspace"  September to January 2nd / Spring Semester   February to July &nb;sp; Application Deadlines Applications for the Spring Semester must be received no later than  31st October . Applications for the year exchange or Autumn Semester must be received no later than  15th May . &nb;sp; Living Costs Accommodation: 200 Euros / month Food: 200 Euros / month Transport: 100 Euros / month Electricity + Water: 50 Euros / month Extras: 50 Euros / month Total Cost of Living per month: 600 Euros/ month   Mr. Arvind Sivamani  Liaison Officer (Outgoing Students)  